  "text": "The three core streaming topology abstractions in Apache Kafka Streams are:\n\n1. **Topology** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/Topology.java)\n   - A public class that defines the DAG (directed acyclic graph) of processing nodes\n   - Contains an InternalTopologyBuilder that manages the graph structure\n   - Serves as the foundation for defining stream processing topologies\n   - Can be passed to KafkaStreams for execution\n\n2. **StreamsBuilder** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/StreamsBuilder.java)\n   - A public class that provides the DSL (Domain-Specific Language) for building topologies\n   - Wraps a Topology instance and provides high-level API methods\n   - Allows developers to define stream processing logic using methods like stream(), table(), etc.\n   - The build() method returns the underlying Topology object\n\n3. **KafkaStreams** (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489: streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/KafkaStreams.java)\n   - A public class implementing AutoCloseable that serves as the runtime for executing topologies\n   - Accepts a Topology and Properties configuration in its constructor\n   - Manages StreamThread instances that process the topology\n   - Provides methods like start(), stop(), and close() to control the application lifecycle\n   - Handles rebalancing and manages the overall Kafka Streams application state"
